-- FACTBOX: Five facts about P&G's Robert McDonald
-- 
-- Tue Dec 8, 2009 11:00am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/12/08/us-procter-factbox-idUSTRE5B73AS20091208

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Procter & Gamble Co said on Tuesday that President and Chief Executive Robert McDonald would become chairman as of January 1, 2010, replacing A.G. Lafley, who will retire from the company early next year. 

 Here are five facts about McDonald: * Robert McDonald was born June 20, 1953, in Gary, Indiana, and grew up in Chicago. * He graduated from the U.S. Military Academy at West Point in 1975 and got his MBA from the University of Utah in 1978. * McDonald served as a U.S. Army captain from 1975-1980, primarily in the 82nd Airborne Division. * He joined Cincinnati-based P&G on June 4, 1980. * McDonald has held several positions at P&G in the United States, Canada, Japan, Korea, Philippines and Belgium. He was named vice chairman of global operations in 2004 and became chief operating officer in 2007. He became president and CEO on July 1, 2009. (Source: P&G; Reporting by Jessica Wohl; Editing by Maureen Bavdek)